I have thrown the Ta Sunke Ska Olowan to the ground... I have scorned a fellow warrior, Kola Icamani, a quiet brother who walked alongside of me.  I must remember that only foolish, frightened women and children shout.<br><br>
I will understand why others look away from me.<br><br>
&quot;Hunhunhe,&quot;  I am astonished and sorrowful!  I am Kaonspe, one who teaches with force.  I am like &quot;Makamnaya,&quot; those who go smelling like a skunk.<br><br>
Was'te sni', it is not good.  Hecito Yelo, I speak the truth.<br><br>
Tatekohomni Wambli<br><br>

